<p>Firestore is a NoSQL (‚Äúnon-relational‚Äù or ‚ÄúNot only SQL‚Äù), document-oriented database.</p>

<p>4 different NoSQL databases can be categorized:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="">Wide column like Cassandra</a></li>
  <li><a href="">Document like MongoDB, Apache CouchDB or Firestore‚Ä¶</a></li>
  <li><a href="">Key‚Äìvalue like Redis</a></li>
  <li><a href="">Graph like InfiniteGraph</a></li>
</ul>

<p>Firestore list documents because it encapsulates and encode information using XML, YAML, and JSON and binary forms like BSON via a unique key that represents that document.</p>
